<paragraph id="8B984F68FFA6FF8DFF05FA866B951876" blockId="4.[150,1438,324,1896]" pageId="4" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="B953937AFFA6FF8DFF05FA866E391A49" bold="true" box="[198,367,1290,1316]" pageId="4" pageNumber="22">Relationships</emphasis>
:— 
<taxonomicName id="4C2734EBFFA6FF8DFE56FA876CD41A49" authorityName="M. J. Silva &amp; Esser" authorityYear="2011" box="[405,898,1290,1316]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Microstachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="ditassoides" subSpecies="villosa">
<emphasis id="B953937AFFA6FF8DFE56FA876D901A49" box="[405,710,1291,1316]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="22">Microstachys ditassoides</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="B953937AFFA6FF8DFCF7FA876CD41A49" box="[820,898,1291,1316]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="22">villosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to typical 
<taxonomicName id="4C2734EBFFA6FF8DFABFFA876C511A26" authority="(Didrichsen 1853: 88) Esser (1998: 958)" authorityName="Esser" authorityPageNumber="958" authorityYear="1998" baseAuthorityName="Didrichsen" baseAuthorityPageNumber="88" baseAuthorityYear="1853" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Microstachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ditassoides">
<emphasis id="B953937AFFA6FF8DFABFFA876E4C1A27" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="22">M. ditassoides</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFB63299FFA6FF8DFEE9FABD6D481A26" author="Didrichsen, D. F." box="[298,542,1329,1355]" pageId="4" pageNumber="22" pagination="86 - 89" refId="ref4211" refString="Didrichsen, D. F. (1853) Plantas nonnullas musei Universitatis Hauniensis. Videnskabelige meddelelser fra den Naturhistoriske Forening i Kjobenhavn 5: 86 - 89." type="journal article" year="1853">Didrichsen 1853: 88</bibRefCitation>
) 
<bibRefCitation id="EFB63299FFA6FF8DFDF3FABD6C511A26" author="Esser, H. - J." box="[560,775,1329,1355]" pageId="4" pageNumber="22" pagination="955 - 960" refId="ref4280" refString="Esser, H. - J. (1998) New combinations in Microstachys (Euphorbiaceae). Kew Bulletin 53: 955 - 960." type="journal article" year="1998">Esser (1998: 958)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. It can, however, easily be distinguished by the densely villous branches and leaves, the latter with flat margins and sparsely serrate (
<emphasis id="B953937AFFA6FF8DFBD5FAD46B781A1C" box="[1046,1070,1368,1393]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="22">vs</emphasis>
. strongly revolute and entire in 
<taxonomicName id="4C2734EBFFA6FF8DFF54FAF36E141AF5" authorityName="Esser" authorityYear="1998" baseAuthorityName="Didrichsen" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[151,322,1406,1432]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Microstachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ditassoides">
<emphasis id="B953937AFFA6FF8DFF54FAF36FF91AF5" box="[151,175,1407,1432]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="22">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B953937AFFA6FF8DFF7CFAF36E141AF5" box="[191,322,1407,1432]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="22">ditassoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), staminate sepals oblong-obovate and obtuse at the apex (
<emphasis id="B953937AFFA6FF8DFBC7FAF36B4A1AF5" box="[1028,1052,1407,1432]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="22">vs</emphasis>
. suborbicular and emarginate at the apex), pistillate sepals glabrous outside and with two basal-lateral, cylindrical and well-developed glands (
<emphasis id="B953937AFFA6FF8DFF62FA406FEF1A88" box="[161,185,1484,1509]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="22">vs</emphasis>
. pistillate sepals pubescent, glands flattened and rudimentary). The leaves are ovate with a broadly cordate base and are villous on both surfaces, which also distinguishes 
<taxonomicName id="4C2734EBFFA6FF8DFC45FA7E6B711961" authorityName="M. J. Silva &amp; Esser" authorityYear="2011" box="[902,1063,1522,1548]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Microstachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="ditassoides" subSpecies="villosa">
subsp. 
<emphasis id="B953937AFFA6FF8DFC1AFA7F6B711961" box="[985,1063,1523,1548]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="22">villosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from typical 
<taxonomicName id="4C2734EBFFA6FF8DFB0AFA7F6A221961" authorityName="Esser" authorityYear="1998" baseAuthorityName="Didrichsen" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[1225,1396,1523,1548]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Microstachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ditassoides">
<emphasis id="B953937AFFA6FF8DFB0AFA7F6A221961" box="[1225,1396,1523,1548]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="22">M. ditassoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C2734EBFFA6FF8DFF54F9956E15195F" authorityName="Esser" authorityYear="1998" baseAuthorityName="Didrichsen" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[151,323,1561,1586]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Microstachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ditassoides">
<emphasis id="B953937AFFA6FF8DFF54F9956E15195F" box="[151,323,1561,1586]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="22">M. ditassoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2602E01FFA6FF8DFE88F9956EDC195E" box="[331,394,1561,1587]" pageId="4" pageNumber="22" sensu="stricto">s. str.</taxonomicNameLabel>
the leaves are ovate-lanceolate or linear with the base cordate to sagittate, glabrous on both surfaces or tomentose on the lower surface only. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2734EBFFA6FF8DFCCBF9CC6B781934" authorityName="Esser" authorityYear="1998" baseAuthorityName="Didrichsen" baseAuthorityYear="1853" box="[776,1070,1600,1625]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Microstachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ditassoides">
<emphasis id="B953937AFFA6FF8DFCCBF9CC6B781934" box="[776,1070,1600,1625]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="22">Microstachys ditassoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized as a specific complex that includes specimens which are usually caespitose, glabrous or densely tomentose but never villous, with ovate leaves which are basally cordate to sagittate, glabrous to tomentose on the lower surface, short to long (to 
<quantity id="4CDFE28DFFA6FF8DFE9CF9386ECD19A3" box="[351,411,1716,1742]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="22" unit="cm" value="8.0">8 cm</quantity>
) inflorescences, and glabrous to tomentose ovary. The typical species occurs in rocky fields and savannas mostly in the states of Minas Gerais, Goias, Bahia and São Paulo, but it also reaches 
<collectingCountry id="F3300FF8FFA6FF8DFF54F88D6FA71876" box="[151,241,1793,1819]" name="Bolivia" pageId="4" pageNumber="22">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C2734EBFFA6FF8DFF3FF88D6D9F1877" authorityName="M. J. Silva &amp; Esser" authorityYear="2011" box="[252,713,1793,1819]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Microstachys" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="22" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="ditassoides" subSpecies="villosa">
<emphasis id="B953937AFFA6FF8DFF3FF88D6D741877" box="[252,546,1793,1818]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="22">Microstachys ditassoides</emphasis>
subsp. 
<emphasis id="B953937AFFA6FF8DFDB8F88D6D9F1877" box="[635,713,1793,1818]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="22">villosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is, however, restricted to the state of Piauí.
</paragraph>
